1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
When galaxies look redder, space itself has stretched their light.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,400
This phenomenon is called 'cosmological redshift'.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:11,200
As the universe expands, light from distant galaxies shifts to longer wavelengths.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:16,000
The further away a galaxy is, the more redshifted its light appears.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,400
This helps astronomers measure the universe's expansion rate, revealing its vastness.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,800
Want to explore more cosmic mysteries?

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,000
Follow for more!
